=== SERVER MODE HIRE BUTTON FIX ===
Date: 2026-03-04
Instance: HK-47 (Mac)

PROBLEM IDENTIFIED:
- Game was running in SERVER mode, not LOCAL mode
- Hire button was calling GameState.hire_worker() which only works in LOCAL mode
- Worker candidates were being generated locally, without server IDs
- In SERVER mode, candidates must be fetched from server API

CHANGES MADE:

1. workers_tab.gd::_generate_candidates()
   - Now checks BackendManager.current_mode
   - SERVER mode: calls _fetch_server_candidates() to get workers from API
   - LOCAL mode: generates workers locally as before

2. workers_tab.gd::_fetch_server_candidates() [NEW FUNCTION]
   - Calls server_backend.get_available_workers()
   - Converts server JSON data to Worker objects
   - Populates server_id field for each worker

3. workers_tab.gd::_hire_candidate()
   - SERVER mode: calls GameState.hire_worker_any_mode(worker.server_id)
   - LOCAL mode: calls GameState.hire_worker(worker) as before

4. workers_tab.gd::EventBus.worker_hired signal handler
   - SERVER mode: refetches candidates from server
   - LOCAL mode: generates new random candidate as before

EXPECTED RESULT:
- Hire button should now work in SERVER mode
- Clicking hire will send POST request to /game/hire with worker_id
- Server will add worker to player's roster
- Next state sync will show hired worker in crew list

TEST PROCEDURE:
1. Open Workers tab
2. Click "New Candidates" button
3. Verify candidates appear (fetched from server)
4. Click "Hire" on a candidate
5. Verify worker appears in crew list after state refresh
